Example 2:
topic: (for) long ▪ (for) a long time
1. Both (for) long and (for) a long time are used as expressions of time. In positive sentences (for) a long time is used.
2. (For) long is not used in positive sentences unless it is used with too, enough, as, so, seldom, etc.
3. Both (for) long and (for) a long time can be used in questions, but (for) long is usually preferred.
4. In negative sentences (for) a long time sometimes has a different meaning from (for) long.

